    "description": "Write a Python function called `iterate_triangular` that must use iter() and next() to visit every value and calculate the triangular total from zero through its absolute value. Use iterator syntax.\nDifficulty: Intermediate.\nExamples:\n  iterate_triangular([5, -4, 0]) -> [15, 10, 0]\n  iterate_triangular([0, 5]) -> [0, 15]",
    "initialCode": "def iterate_triangular(values):\n    pass",
    "solution": "# Using function approach\n# Example 1: canonical iterator solution\ndef iterate_triangular(values):\n    iterator = iter(values)\n    result = []\n    while True:\n        try:\n            item = next(iterator)\n        except StopIteration:\n            break\n        result.append(abs(item) * (abs(item) + 1) // 2)\n    return result\n\nprint(iterate_triangular([5, -4, 0]))  # Expected: [15, 10, 0]\nprint(iterate_triangular([0, 5]))  # Expected: [0, 15]\n\n# Example 2: nested helper approach\ndef solve_problem_2876(values):\n    def execute():\n        iterator = iter(values)\n        result = []\n        while True:\n            try:\n                item = next(iterator)\n            except StopIteration:\n                break\n            result.append(abs(item) * (abs(item) + 1) // 2)\n        return result\n    return execute()\n\nprint(solve_problem_2876([5, -4, 0]))\n\n# Example 3: static method approach\nclass Problem2876Solution:\n    @staticmethod\n    def iterate_triangular(values):\n        iterator = iter(values)\n        result = []\n        while True:\n            try:\n                item = next(iterator)\n            except StopIteration:\n                break\n            result.append(abs(item) * (abs(item) + 1) // 2)\n        return result\n\nprint(Problem2876Solution.iterate_triangular([0, 5]))\n\n# Example 4: assigned result approach\nresult = iterate_triangular([5, -4, 0])\nprint(result)\n\n# Example 5: direct call\nprint(iterate_triangular([-4]))",
