    "solution": "# Using function approach\n# Example 1: canonical context manager solution\ndef managed_running_total(value):\n    class ManagedValue:\n        def __init__(self, stored):\n            self.stored = stored\n\n        def __enter__(self):\n            return self.stored\n\n        def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_value, traceback):\n            return False\n\n    with ManagedValue(value) as current:\n        result = [sum(current[:index + 1]) for index in range(len(current))]\n    return result\n\nprint(managed_running_total([1, 2, 3]))  # Expected: [1, 3, 6]\nprint(managed_running_total([-2, 0, 5]))  # Expected: [-2, -2, 3]\n\n# Example 2: nested helper approach\ndef solve_problem_2955(value):\n    def execute():\n        class ManagedValue:\n            def __init__(self, stored):\n                self.stored = stored\n    \n            def __enter__(self):\n                return self.stored\n    \n            def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_value, traceback):\n                return False\n    \n        with ManagedValue(value) as current:\n            result = [sum(current[:index + 1]) for index in range(len(current))]\n        return result\n    return execute()\n\nprint(solve_problem_2955([1, 2, 3]))\n\n# Example 3: static method approach\nclass Problem2955Solution:\n    @staticmethod\n    def managed_running_total(value):\n        class ManagedValue:\n            def __init__(self, stored):\n                self.stored = stored\n    \n            def __enter__(self):\n                return self.stored\n    \n            def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_value, traceback):\n                return False\n    \n        with ManagedValue(value) as current:\n            result = [sum(current[:index + 1]) for index in range(len(current))]\n        return result\n\nprint(Problem2955Solution.managed_running_total([-2, 0, 5]))\n\n# Example 4: assigned result approach\nresult = managed_running_total([1, 2, 3])\nprint(result)\n\n# Example 5: direct call\nprint(managed_running_total([3, 3, 1]))",
