    "description": "Write a Python function called `pipeline_running_total` that must apply a result-transforming decorator that will return all running totals. Use decorator syntax.\nDifficulty: Difficult.\nExamples:\n  pipeline_running_total([1, 2, 3]) -> [1, 3, 6]\n  pipeline_running_total([-2, 0, 5]) -> [-2, -2, 3]",
    "initialCode": "def pipeline_running_total(value):\n    pass",
    "solution": "# Using function approach\n# Example 1: canonical decorator solution\ndef pipeline_running_total(value):\n    def apply_transform(function):\n        def wrapped(value):\n            original = function(value)\n            return [sum(original[:index + 1]) for index in range(len(original))]\n        return wrapped\n\n    @apply_transform\n    def preserve(value):\n        return value\n\n    return preserve(value)\n\nprint(pipeline_running_total([1, 2, 3]))  # Expected: [1, 3, 6]\nprint(pipeline_running_total([-2, 0, 5]))  # Expected: [-2, -2, 3]\n\n# Example 2: nested helper approach\ndef solve_problem_3155(value):\n    def execute():\n        def apply_transform(function):\n            def wrapped(value):\n                original = function(value)\n                return [sum(original[:index + 1]) for index in range(len(original))]\n            return wrapped\n    \n        @apply_transform\n        def preserve(value):\n            return value\n    \n        return preserve(value)\n    return execute()\n\nprint(solve_problem_3155([1, 2, 3]))\n\n# Example 3: static method approach\nclass Problem3155Solution:\n    @staticmethod\n    def pipeline_running_total(value):\n        def apply_transform(function):\n            def wrapped(value):\n                original = function(value)\n                return [sum(original[:index + 1]) for index in range(len(original))]\n            return wrapped\n    \n        @apply_transform\n        def preserve(value):\n            return value\n    \n        return preserve(value)\n\nprint(Problem3155Solution.pipeline_running_total([-2, 0, 5]))\n\n# Example 4: assigned result approach\nresult = pipeline_running_total([1, 2, 3])\nprint(result)\n\n# Example 5: direct call\nprint(pipeline_running_total([3, 3, 1]))",
