    "description": "Write a Python function called `pipeline_index_pairs` that must apply a result-transforming decorator that will pair every item with its zero-based index. Use decorator syntax.\nDifficulty: Difficult.\nExamples:\n  pipeline_index_pairs([1, 2, 3]) -> [[0, 1], [1, 2], [2, 3]]\n  pipeline_index_pairs([-2, 0, 5]) -> [[0, -2], [1, 0], [2, 5]]",
    "initialCode": "def pipeline_index_pairs(value):\n    pass",
    "solution": "# Using function approach\n# Example 1: canonical decorator solution\ndef pipeline_index_pairs(value):\n    def apply_transform(function):\n        def wrapped(value):\n            original = function(value)\n            return list(enumerate(original))\n        return wrapped\n\n    @apply_transform\n    def preserve(value):\n        return value\n\n    return preserve(value)\n\nprint(pipeline_index_pairs([1, 2, 3]))  # Expected: [[0, 1], [1, 2], [2, 3]]\nprint(pipeline_index_pairs([-2, 0, 5]))  # Expected: [[0, -2], [1, 0], [2, 5]]\n\n# Example 2: nested helper approach\ndef solve_problem_3156(value):\n    def execute():\n        def apply_transform(function):\n            def wrapped(value):\n                original = function(value)\n                return list(enumerate(original))\n            return wrapped\n    \n        @apply_transform\n        def preserve(value):\n            return value\n    \n        return preserve(value)\n    return execute()\n\nprint(solve_problem_3156([1, 2, 3]))\n\n# Example 3: static method approach\nclass Problem3156Solution:\n    @staticmethod\n    def pipeline_index_pairs(value):\n        def apply_transform(function):\n            def wrapped(value):\n                original = function(value)\n                return list(enumerate(original))\n            return wrapped\n    \n        @apply_transform\n        def preserve(value):\n            return value\n    \n        return preserve(value)\n\nprint(Problem3156Solution.pipeline_index_pairs([-2, 0, 5]))\n\n# Example 4: assigned result approach\nresult = pipeline_index_pairs([1, 2, 3])\nprint(result)\n\n# Example 5: direct call\nprint(pipeline_index_pairs([3, 3, 1]))",
